#!/bin/sh
# Commit message template for UDD project
# Use Conventional Commits as the base: https://www.conventionalcommits.org/
# Example: feat(scope): short description [health:✓]
#   - type: feat, fix, chore, docs, refactor, test, perf, ci
#   - scope: optional (area or package)
#   - description: concise imperative summary (max ~72 chars)
# Health indicator legend:
#   [health:✓]  - All health checks passed (udd doctor, no stub assertions)
#   [health:⚠]  - Warnings present (non-critical; please investigate)
#   [health:✗]  - Blocking issues detected (do not push until resolved)
#
# BEFORE YOU COMMIT
# 1) Run the health checks locally:
#      udd doctor        # quick diagnostic
#      udd status        # confirm journey/scenario/test coverage
# 2) Ensure there are no stub assertions in Phase 3 tests:
#      rg "expect(true).toBe(true)" tests/ || true
#    If any are present, either replace with a real assertion or tag the
#    scenario with @phase:4 and open an issue tracking completion.
# 3) Run relevant tests (or the smoke test):
#      bun run test       # or `bun run test:smoke` if available
#
# Commit message format (one-line summary, optional body)
# -------------------------------------------------------
# <type>(<scope>): <short description> [health:✓|⚠|✗]
#
# Long description / details (optional):
# - Explain WHY the change was made, not HOW.
# - Reference related journeys, feature files, or issue IDs when applicable.
# - If you deliberately bypassed a health check, explain why and link issue.
#
# Examples:
# feat(auth): add token refresh endpoint [health:✓]
# fix(cli): handle missing config file gracefully [health:⚠]
# docs: update onboarding guide for API keys [health:✓]

# ---------------- (END TEMPLATE) ----------------
